♪ Why don't you turn
your life around ♪

01:25.227 --> 01:28.631
Hey, I'm Dane Marbeck or
you can call me Marbles.

01:28.665 --> 01:30.433
I beg your pardon?

01:30.467 --> 01:32.702
So, who died?

01:32.735 --> 01:34.871
My niece, Nikita.

01:34.904 --> 01:36.406
My husband, Jack.

01:36.439 --> 01:37.774
My Reg.

01:37.807 --> 01:39.241
Someone who cut my hair.

01:39.274 --> 01:42.010
Well, someone who
used to cut my hair

01:42.044 --> 01:43.613
and then, you know.

01:45.214 --> 01:46.716
Do you want to
apologize to them,

01:46.749 --> 01:48.250
or do you want to
confess something,

01:48.283 --> 01:51.220
or maybe you just want to give
them permission to pass over?

01:51.253 --> 01:52.789
What do you mean?

01:52.822 --> 01:54.256
To the next plane.

01:54.289 --> 01:56.258
What's the next plane?

01:57.259 --> 01:58.628
I don't know.

01:58.661 --> 01:59.796
But she might have stayed?

01:59.829 --> 02:01.431
Of course, it
depends on the deceased

02:01.464 --> 02:04.767
'cause they have to actively
choose to pass over.

02:04.801 --> 02:06.001
I don't get it.

02:06.034 --> 02:07.871
It's kind of like
there's this great party

02:07.904 --> 02:09.137
and you've been forced to leave,

02:09.170 --> 02:10.406
but you don't want
to leave the party.

02:10.440 --> 02:13.075
She'd never
like to leave a party.

02:13.108 --> 02:14.343
Well, there you go.

02:14.377 --> 02:16.011
Here she goes.

02:16.044 --> 02:17.480
What's that?

02:17.514 --> 02:19.816
It's what makes talking
with ghosts possible.

02:19.849 --> 02:20.683
Ready?

02:40.168 --> 02:42.170
Can you see me?

02:42.204 --> 02:43.573
He's still naked.

02:43.606 --> 02:44.941
You can see him?

02:44.974 --> 02:45.775
He's here?

02:47.010 --> 02:48.611
Hello.

02:48.645 --> 02:50.078
My name is Marbles.

02:50.112 --> 02:52.214
- So his name's Jack?
- Jack, yep.

02:52.247 --> 02:53.148
Jack, okay,

02:53.181 --> 02:54.182
and it happened over there?

02:54.216 --> 02:56.118
Yep, just there.

02:56.151 --> 02:57.319
Okay.

03:00.355 --> 03:02.324
Something's wrong.

03:06.696 --> 03:08.063
Can I speak to her?

03:08.096 --> 03:09.331
Yeah, of course,

03:09.364 --> 03:12.669
but you'll have to talk through me.
I'll be like a condweet.

03:12.702 --> 03:14.037
A what?

03:14.069 --> 03:14.938
A condweet?

03:14.971 --> 03:16.338
Yeah, a condweet.

03:16.371 --> 03:17.774
You talk to me and I'll,

03:17.807 --> 03:19.742
you tell me and I'll tell her.

03:19.776 --> 03:21.143
Oh, you mean a conduit.

03:21.176 --> 03:22.812
Of
course, a conduit.

03:22.845 --> 03:24.447
You mean a conduit.

03:24.480 --> 03:25.715
Yeah.

03:29.217 --> 03:30.486
What's wrong?

03:30.520 --> 03:32.021
How long ago did
your girlfriend die?

03:32.055 --> 03:33.990
Girlfriend?
I wouldn't say she's my girlfriend.

03:34.023 --> 03:34.924
She's just someone...

03:34.958 --> 03:36.459
Yeah, but how long
ago did it happen?

03:36.492 --> 03:37.660
It's not good you
sticking around.

03:37.694 --> 03:39.596
It's not good you
sticking around here.

03:39.629 --> 03:42.364
A couple, eight months.

03:42.398 --> 03:45.068
Oh my god, you should have
called me as soon as it happened.

03:45.100 --> 03:47.637
We need to get her
to want to pass over.

03:47.670 --> 03:49.405
I don't want her to pass over.

03:49.439 --> 03:50.907
So this is like
a bathroom, is it?

03:50.940 --> 03:53.275
- Yeah, but...
- But there's another bathroom in the house?

03:53.308 --> 03:54.209
Yeah.

03:54.242 --> 03:56.278
Use that I reckon, use that.

03:56.311 --> 03:58.313
Okay, anyway, mate,

03:58.347 --> 04:00.315
listen, no charge.

04:00.349 --> 04:02.184
Your house is fine.

04:02.217 --> 04:03.419
Okay, you know bananas

04:03.453 --> 04:05.388
when they get like
really old and spotty

04:05.421 --> 04:07.023
and they go all black
and then they shrivel up,

04:07.056 --> 04:10.627
and they make all the other
fruit in the bowl go black?

04:10.660 --> 04:11.461
Yeah.

04:14.530 --> 04:16.065
Jack?

04:16.099 --> 04:17.033
Jackie boy?

04:18.668 --> 04:20.403
I mean, it's a good
thing he's not here

04:20.435 --> 04:23.806
'cause that'll mean he's
probably passed over,

04:23.840 --> 04:25.041
which means he's had a good life

04:25.074 --> 04:26.308
and he's had no
regrets, you know?

04:26.341 --> 04:27.777
So that's a good thing.

04:27.810 --> 04:29.479
If you ever feel an
oppressive presence

04:29.512 --> 04:31.279
that makes you feel real bad,

04:31.313 --> 04:34.316
like there's a deep
darkness in your soul,

04:34.349 --> 04:35.618
give me a call.

04:36.686 --> 04:37.787
Okay.

04:37.820 --> 04:40.155
What, more than normal?

04:40.188 --> 04:42.290
Oh, no charge honestly.

04:45.662 --> 04:47.096
I just,

04:47.130 --> 04:49.231
I just wanted one more chance
to say something to him,

04:49.264 --> 04:50.066
you know?

04:50.099 --> 04:53.102
Yeah, I know.

04:55.938 --> 04:58.708
So he's very close
to you right now.

04:58.741 --> 05:00.910
He's just a few inches
away from your face.

05:00.943 --> 05:04.414
My dear.

05:07.583 --> 05:08.418
Marbeck.

05:09.619 --> 05:10.853
You can see me.

05:12.354 --> 05:13.556
I've paid all my bills.

05:13.589 --> 05:14.791
I've arranged
everything for her.

05:14.824 --> 05:16.025
Excuse me, sir.

05:16.059 --> 05:18.193
I just need to talk to this gentleman.
Marbeck...

05:18.226 --> 05:19.729
It's probably
not for you, mate.

05:19.762 --> 05:23.399
Phillis, I'm just gonna step
outside for a few seconds

05:23.433 --> 05:25.200
just to give you guys
a bit of alone time.

05:25.233 --> 05:30.139
So, he can hear everything
that you're gonna say, okay?

05:30.173 --> 05:31.174
Thank you.

05:34.110 --> 05:36.244
This is a miracle.

05:36.278 --> 05:37.680
Yeah.

05:37.714 --> 05:38.748
Okay, listen, we need to talk.

05:38.781 --> 05:40.183
My name is Officer Jayson Tagg...

05:40.215 --> 05:41.617
Of the Aotearoa
Police Service.

05:41.651 --> 05:42.452
I know.

05:42.485 --> 05:43.653
You've arrested me once.

05:43.686 --> 05:45.320
- I know you've got something!
- You're tickling me!

05:45.353 --> 05:46.389
You're tickling me!

05:46.422 --> 05:47.523
Hey, then what's this?

05:47.557 --> 05:48.458
What is this?

05:48.491 --> 05:49.926
I use that to see ghosts!

05:49.959 --> 05:51.427
I think I've searched
you a couple of times,

05:51.461 --> 05:53.763
but no, I've never charged you.

05:53.796 --> 05:56.065
What happened, man?

05:56.099 --> 05:56.899
Murdered.

05:56.933 --> 05:57.700
What?

05:57.734 --> 05:58.935
On a case.

05:58.968 --> 05:59.969
Whoa, man.

06:00.903 --> 06:02.505
That's a bum hole.

06:02.538 --> 06:05.340
Yeah, it's a bum hole.

06:05.373 --> 06:07.577
How are you feeling about it?
Are you okay?

06:07.610 --> 06:10.747
Is there anybody else
that I can talk to?

06:10.780 --> 06:12.849
Well no, I think it's just me.

06:12.882 --> 06:14.249
Okay.

06:14.282 --> 06:15.618
In that case then,
listen, I need your help.

06:15.651 --> 06:16.452
Yeah, of course, man.

06:16.486 --> 06:17.887
What do you need?

06:19.088 --> 06:21.791
I'm gonna hunt the man
responsible for my death

06:21.824 --> 06:23.126
and take him down.

06:25.728 --> 06:27.797
Yeah,

06:27.830 --> 06:29.165
I'm not gonna do that.

06:29.198 --> 06:30.700
He's killed six
people already.

06:30.733 --> 06:31.834
I am number seven.

06:31.868 --> 06:33.402
- Yeah, all right.
- Listen.

06:33.436 --> 06:34.937
I've got some life insurance.

06:34.971 --> 06:38.808
Hey, we can find a way to
cut you in on some of it.

06:38.841 --> 06:40.810
But what about
your family, man?

06:40.843 --> 06:42.945
Listen, the killer
dropped some evidence.

06:42.979 --> 06:44.247
Do you have any family?

06:44.279 --> 06:45.347
Yeah, I've got
a foster sister.

06:45.381 --> 06:46.348
She doesn't need the money.

06:46.382 --> 06:47.850
Okay.

06:47.884 --> 06:50.153
That's who you need to focus
on right now, mate, okay?

06:50.186 --> 06:52.989
And I can be that conduit
between you and her.

06:53.022 --> 06:54.957
I can be there for you.

06:58.326 --> 06:59.228
Dane Marbeck.

06:59.262 --> 07:00.062
That's your name, isn't it?

07:00.096 --> 07:00.997
Can I call you Dane?

07:01.030 --> 07:01.898
Call me Marbles, man.

07:01.931 --> 07:02.899
Everyone does.

07:02.932 --> 07:04.100
It's my nickname.

07:04.133 --> 07:06.636
Listen, if you help
me find this guy,

07:06.669 --> 07:10.273
you could be a hero,
a national hero.

07:10.305 --> 07:12.742
What do you think about that?

07:14.210 --> 07:18.281
Yeah, I just help the
dead find peace, okay?

07:18.313 --> 07:20.650
I don't help hunt the living

07:20.683 --> 07:23.386
or with murder
cases or whatever,

07:23.419 --> 07:25.521
so good luck to you, man.

07:27.089 --> 07:29.725
Dane, he's already
killed six people!

07:29.759 --> 07:32.295
He's gonna keep on killing
people until you help me!

07:32.327 --> 07:33.162
Dane!

07:35.031 --> 07:38.801
Tell her that I was really
sorry that I took the bath.

07:38.835 --> 07:40.335
I just love baths.

07:40.368 --> 07:42.471
He knows it was really dumb
but it was a really good bath.

07:42.505 --> 07:45.340
And I do
love you so much.

07:46.676 --> 07:48.010
He does love you.

07:48.044 --> 07:49.779
And that she's crazy,

07:49.812 --> 07:51.581
and she's the smartest

07:51.614 --> 07:54.150
and the silliest
person I've ever met.

07:54.183 --> 07:55.418
And she knows...

07:57.286 --> 07:58.988
You're the most beautiful,

07:59.021 --> 08:01.924
spectacular person
he's ever known.

08:05.194 --> 08:07.630
I have to go, I think.

08:28.751 --> 08:30.086
I felt him go.

08:35.758 --> 08:36.592
Thank you.

08:41.163 --> 08:43.765
You spent an hour talking
with an old dead man

08:43.799 --> 08:45.501
and an old nearly dead woman.

08:45.534 --> 08:47.169
- What you should...
- Peanut brownie?

08:47.203 --> 08:48.871
No, I can't.

08:48.905 --> 08:50.106
What you could be doing

08:50.139 --> 08:52.241
is helping me effect
some real change...

08:54.810 --> 08:57.747
A hit usually
lasts about an hour.

08:57.780 --> 08:59.715
Sayonara, Officer Tagg.

09:23.039 --> 09:25.474
Dane, Dane, listen to me.

09:25.508 --> 09:27.176
It's a piece of paper.

09:27.209 --> 09:29.045
Look, all you have to
do is go to the scene,

09:29.078 --> 09:31.747
grab a piece of paper,
take it to my sister,

09:31.781 --> 09:33.582
and you could be a hero.

09:33.616 --> 09:35.918
Are you even hearing...?

09:35.952 --> 09:36.786
Dane.

09:50.633 --> 09:53.502
♪ My baby ♪

09:59.308 --> 10:00.876
Hey, Xavier, man.

10:00.910 --> 10:01.777
What's up?

10:01.811 --> 10:03.245
Hey, man.

10:03.279 --> 10:04.947
Where have you been?

10:06.615 --> 10:08.918
Just here working and stuff,

10:08.951 --> 10:10.420
and around.

10:10.454 --> 10:12.288
You were meant to
help me set up this afternoon.

10:12.321 --> 10:14.090
Oh man,
I totally forgot.

10:14.123 --> 10:15.057
Sorry, bro.

10:16.625 --> 10:18.527
Are you gonna let me in or?

10:18.561 --> 10:19.695
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

10:19.729 --> 10:20.529
Sorry.

10:20.563 --> 10:22.198
Come on in.

10:22.231 --> 10:25.167
Yeah, just grab a
seat if you want.

10:28.838 --> 10:31.240
I'll just grab the cash.

10:39.383 --> 10:40.850
Oh, thanks man.

10:40.883 --> 10:41.951
Disgusting.

10:41.984 --> 10:44.320
There you go.

10:44.353 --> 10:47.256
So, I have a
birthday coming up.

10:47.289 --> 10:48.324
Oh, cool.

10:48.357 --> 10:50.126
How old are you turning?

10:50.159 --> 10:51.560
30.

10:51.594 --> 10:54.464
That's what the
party's for, remember?

10:54.498 --> 10:56.400
Are you going to come or not?

10:56.433 --> 10:57.467
When is it?

10:59.268 --> 11:01.303
Man, I knew you wouldn't come.

11:01.337 --> 11:02.472
No, I'll come.

11:02.506 --> 11:03.539
Just when is it?

11:03.572 --> 11:06.042
Nevermind, I get it.

11:06.075 --> 11:07.109
Okay, cool.

11:13.315 --> 11:14.817
Let's get to work.

