11:19.389 --> 11:20.723
♪ Our love is a boogeyman ♪

11:20.756 --> 11:22.058
♪ My love, your love ♪

11:22.091 --> 11:25.294
♪ Our love is a boogeyman ♪

11:26.762 --> 11:28.064
♪ My love, your love ♪

11:28.097 --> 11:29.732
♪ Our love is a boogeyman ♪

11:29.765 --> 11:31.133
♪ My love, your love ♪

11:31.167 --> 11:32.701
♪ Our love is a boogeyman ♪

11:32.735 --> 11:34.770
Dane Marbeck.

11:40.410 --> 11:41.243
Mum, hi...

11:42.479 --> 11:43.979
You keep putting that
crap into your body,

11:44.013 --> 11:46.082
you'll turn into a shell.

11:48.984 --> 11:50.753
Who are you?

11:50.786 --> 11:52.254
Xavier, ma'am.

11:52.288 --> 11:55.124
And can I just say what an
honor it is to meet you?

11:55.157 --> 11:57.359
What's with the box, mum?

11:58.260 --> 11:59.895
I had an offer on the farm.

11:59.929 --> 12:01.398
What?

12:01.431 --> 12:03.999
I said I've
had an offer on the farm.

12:04.033 --> 12:05.569
Oh no, I heard you.

12:05.601 --> 12:08.204
Why did you say what then?

12:08.237 --> 12:09.439
Disbelief, maybe.

12:09.473 --> 12:10.574
What, you don't believe me?

12:10.606 --> 12:11.807
No, I believe you.

12:11.841 --> 12:15.111
Why the
disbelief then, Dane?

12:15.144 --> 12:16.612
Hm.

12:16.645 --> 12:18.080
I've given you
more than enough time

12:18.114 --> 12:19.315
to come up with the money,

12:19.348 --> 12:22.918
but this offer means
that I can leave now.

12:22.952 --> 12:25.154
I'm in a good place now.

12:25.187 --> 12:26.322
I can move on.

12:26.355 --> 12:29.859
I just brought you
some of your old stuff.

12:32.027 --> 12:34.697
I'm really happy for you, mum.

12:36.165 --> 12:38.267
How much did they offer if
you don't mind my asking?

12:38.300 --> 12:39.935
You can't afford
to counter it.

12:39.969 --> 12:42.138
Whatever. I just want to
know how much it is, mum.

12:42.171 --> 12:43.105
Don't say whatever, Dane.

12:43.139 --> 12:44.206
It's uncouth.

12:45.509 --> 12:46.675
Sorry.

12:46.709 --> 12:48.978
Don't apologize, just
don't say it again.

12:49.011 --> 12:50.346
Listen, I've been
doing some savings

12:50.380 --> 12:53.182
and I've got not
enough for a deposit.

12:53.215 --> 12:56.051
Why is this so
important to you?

12:58.187 --> 12:59.355
'Cause of...

13:00.689 --> 13:01.591
Speak up.

13:02.691 --> 13:04.494
Well, 'cause of dad.

13:06.228 --> 13:07.531
I didn't even make it in time

13:07.564 --> 13:10.467
to say goodbye
before he, you know.

13:12.636 --> 13:13.869
I'm gonna go.

13:17.373 --> 13:19.808
See you at my party, Marbles.

13:23.179 --> 13:24.013
Dane,

13:25.948 --> 13:28.951
150,000 is a lot
of money, isn't it?

13:34.290 --> 13:36.158
Tell you what.

13:36.192 --> 13:38.794
I'll give you two days to
come up with the money.

13:38.827 --> 13:41.464
After that, it's
out of my hands.

13:41.498 --> 13:42.731
I have to sell.

14:30.112 --> 14:32.114
- Game!
- For god's sake,

14:33.483 --> 14:34.917
go and get ready.

14:36.986 --> 14:38.421
Ross!

14:38.455 --> 14:40.690
We have to be out of here
in 10 minutes. Just go!

14:40.724 --> 14:42.392
Okay,.

14:42.425 --> 14:43.359
Honestly.

14:44.893 --> 14:46.962
Like a bloody teenager!

14:48.364 --> 14:51.033
She loves it, Marbles.

14:59.576 --> 15:00.410
Dane!

15:01.844 --> 15:02.679
Dane!

15:05.548 --> 15:06.949
Oh my god, dad.

15:11.186 --> 15:14.256
I shouldn't have taken
you down to the pond, dad.

15:14.290 --> 15:15.592
Oh, rubbish, rubbish.

15:15.625 --> 15:18.160
No, I really, really enjoyed it.

15:18.193 --> 15:19.763
- Honestly.
- Okay.

15:19.795 --> 15:23.265
Remember I used to take you
down there when you were a kid?

15:23.299 --> 15:24.800
Remember I told you
there were fish in it?

15:29.739 --> 15:31.807
Listen, son, there are
two feelings in this world

15:31.840 --> 15:33.275
that are completely useless

15:33.309 --> 15:35.978
and one of them is regret, okay?

15:39.482 --> 15:44.253
Yeah, 'cause life's...
life's, yeah.

15:47.590 --> 15:49.158
And what's the other feeling?

15:49.191 --> 15:52.462
Dane, get
down here now, Dane.

15:52.495 --> 15:55.598
Sounds ominous.

15:55.632 --> 15:58.635
She doesn't like
when I come over.

15:59.569 --> 16:01.070
She says it makes you tired

16:01.103 --> 16:05.475
and that she says that I'm
not allowed to visit anymore.

16:05.508 --> 16:08.445
Dane, you're
always welcome here.

16:11.681 --> 16:13.849
This is our place.

16:13.882 --> 16:17.219
Dane Marbeck, I am
not asking you a third time!

16:17.252 --> 16:18.087
Go on.

16:28.063 --> 16:32.502
Officer Jayson Tagg of
the Aotearoa Police Service,

16:33.969 --> 16:37.973
how much life insurance
are we talking about?

16:38.006 --> 16:40.008
Atta-boy, Marbeck.

16:44.046 --> 16:46.014
It was a beautiful sunny morning

16:46.048 --> 16:48.083
and I was walking the
beat along Patrick Beach

16:48.117 --> 16:50.653
like I do every week.

16:50.687 --> 16:52.589
The first victim had
been abducted from there

16:52.622 --> 16:54.858
about two years ago

16:54.890 --> 16:57.794
and the perpetrator had
eluded me ever since.

16:57.827 --> 17:00.597
I guess you could say my
instincts were on high alert

17:00.630 --> 17:04.098
and I could just tell that
this guy was bad news.

17:04.133 --> 17:05.968
How did you know?

17:06.001 --> 17:07.368
Instinct.

17:07.404 --> 17:09.204
What, 'cause he
was wearing a hood?

17:09.238 --> 17:11.473
Okay, you wouldn't understand.

17:11.508 --> 17:13.810
Judging people 'cause
of the way they look, hey?

17:13.843 --> 17:14.743
Okay.

17:14.778 --> 17:15.779
You're one of them, Marbeck.

17:15.811 --> 17:17.311
Please call me Marbles, man.

17:17.346 --> 17:19.047
I'm not gonna
call you Marbles.

17:19.080 --> 17:19.883
Hang on.

17:19.915 --> 17:21.417
One of them?

17:21.451 --> 17:23.018
You're a coaster.

17:24.387 --> 17:26.689
What, one of those
things you put a drink on?

17:26.723 --> 17:30.058
No, you're a drainer, a taker.

17:30.092 --> 17:31.927
Okay, there are two types of
people in the world, right?

